      { question: "In the Weber test, sound lateralizes to the left ear. The Rinne test shows bone conduction greater than air conduction on the left. What type of hearing loss is present?", options: ["Left sensorineural hearing loss", "Left conductive hearing loss", "Right conductive hearing loss", "Bilateral sensorineural hearing loss"], correct: 1, rationale: "Weber lateralizing to the affected ear combined with bone conduction greater than air conduction (negative Rinne) indicates conductive hearing loss on that side." }
